    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Quentin P. Gore was an American journalist and editor of the Chicago Sun-Times.  He was also the author of 
<emph render="italic">The Chicago Sun-Times type and makeup manual</emph>. (1964)</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Quentin P. Gore Papers</emph> comprise four series.  <emph render="bold">Miscellaneous</emph> 
contains a movie editing kit.  <emph render="bold">Published material</emph> contains books pertaining to newspaper publishing 
as well as issues of <emph render="italic">Linotype News</emph>, a magazine for those in the printing field.  
<emph render="bold">Subject files</emph> contains mainly correspondence about the <emph render="italic">Chicago Sun-Times</emph>, 
a newspaper edited by Gore.  <emph render="bold">Writings</emph> contains volumes of Gore's <emph render="italic">Typographical 
and makeup manual</emph> as well as a scrapbook of clippings of his column, "The Axis on the Air."</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>Each series is arranged alphabetically by type (Published material), topic (Subject files), or 
title (Writings).</p>
    </arrangement>
